<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-516-147  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 516 147.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 8 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM Japan plans budget Japanese PC next spring. (low-end versionsof IBM PS/55)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Takahashi, Ken.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   IBM Japan Ltd. (products).andO;Product:   IBM PS/55 (Microcomputer) (product enhancement).andO;Topic:     Computer industryJapanSubsidiary corporationsStrategic PlanningMicrocomputersLow Performance Equipment.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IBM JAPAN PLANS BUDGET JAPANESE PC NEXT SPRING TOKYO, JAPAN, 1990 AUG 20 (NB)-- According to The Japan Industrial Journal paper, IBM Japan, the Japanesearm of U.S.-based computer giant IBM, has decided to create new line-up ofbudget personal computers as low-end versions of the current PS/55 series.andM;The paper reports that IBM Japan is expected to market a notebook-sized PC,targeted at individual users, as early as next spring.andM;The PS/55, the Japanese version of the PS/2, is hard to discount due to thecomplicated architecture, so IBM Japan could not price the PS/55Z lower than400,000 yen ($2,700).andP;  As notebook PCs are priced around 200,000 yen ($1,350)in the current market, IBM Japan has judged it necessary to launch a personalcomputer based on a new architecture.andM;There are many IBM PC-compatible machines with Japanese language featuresavailable here in Japan, such as the Toshiba J3100 and AX machines.andP;  TheJapanese computer industry has suggested IBM Japan's new computer will becomejust another PC-DOS machine with Japanese language features.andM;(Ken Takahashi/19900816)</TEXT></DOC>